265 int
266 net_decode_str (char *msg, int msg_size, char *func_code, void ***ret_argv)
267 {
268  int remain_size = msg_size;
269  char *cur_p = msg;
270  char *argp;
271  int i_val;
272  void **argv = NULL;
273  int argc = 0;
274 
275  *ret_argv = (void **) NULL;
276 
277  if (remain_size < 1)
278  return CAS_ER_COMMUNICATION;
279 
280  *func_code = *cur_p;
281  cur_p += 1;
282  remain_size -= 1;
283 
284  while (remain_size > 0)
285  {
286  if (remain_size < 4)
287  {
288  FREE_MEM (argv);
289  return CAS_ER_COMMUNICATION;
290  }
291  argp = cur_p;
292  memcpy ((char *) &i_val, cur_p, 4);
293  i_val = ntohl (i_val);
294  remain_size -= 4;
295  cur_p += 4;
296 
297  if (remain_size < i_val)
298  {
299  FREE_MEM (argv);
300  return CAS_ER_COMMUNICATION;
301  }
302 
303  argc++;
304  argv = (void **) REALLOC (argv, sizeof (void *) * argc);
305  if (argv == NULL)
306  return CAS_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
307 
308  argv[argc - 1] = argp;
309 
310  cur_p += i_val;
311  remain_size -= i_val;
312  }
313 
314  *ret_argv = argv;
315  return argc;
316 }
317 #endif /* if 1 */

319 static int
320 shard_io_set_fl (int fd, int flags)
321 { /* flags are file status flags to turn on */
322 #if defined(WINDOWS)
323  u_long argp;
324 
325  if (flags == O_NONBLOCK)
326  {
327  argp = 1; /* 1:non-blocking, 0:blocking */
328  if (ioctlsocket ((SOCKET) fd, FIONBIO, &argp) == SOCKET_ERROR)
329  {
330  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to ioctlsocket(%d, FIONBIO, %u). " "(error:%d).", fd, argp,
331  SOCKET_ERROR);
332  return -1;
333  }
334  }
335 #else
336  int val;
337 
338  if ((val = fcntl (fd, F_GETFL, 0)) < 0)
339  {
340  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to fcntl(%d, F_GETFL). (val:%d, errno:%d).", fd, val, errno);
341  return -1;
342  }
343 
344  val |= flags; /* turn on flags */
345 
346  if (fcntl (fd, F_SETFL, val) < 0)
347  {
348  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to fcntl(%d, F_SETFL, %d). (errno:%d).", fd, val, errno);
349  return -1;
350  }
351 #endif
352  return 1;
353 }

356 static int
357 shard_io_clr_fl (int fd, int flags)
358 { /* flags are file status flags to turn on */
359 #if defined(WINDOWS)
360  u_long argp;
361 
362  if (flags == O_NONBLOCK)
363  {
364  argp = 0; /* 1:non-blocking, 0:blocking */
365  if (ioctlsocket ((SOCKET) fd, FIONBIO, &argp) == SOCKET_ERROR)
366  {
367  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to ioctlsocket(%d, FIONBIO, %u). (error:%d).", fd, argp,
368  SOCKET_ERROR);
369  return -1;
370  }
371  }
372 #else
373  int val;
374 
375  if ((val = fcntl (fd, F_GETFL, 0)) < 0)
376  {
377  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to fcntl(%d, F_GETFL). (val:%d, errno:%d).", fd, val, errno);
378  return -1;
379  }
380 
381  val &= ~flags; /* turn off flags */
382 
383  if (fcntl (fd, F_SETFL, val) < 0)
384  {
385  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to fcntl(%d, F_SETFL, %d). (errno:%d).", fd, val, errno);
386  return -1;
387  }
388 #endif
389  return 1;
390 }

392 static int
393 shard_io_setsockbuf (int fd, int size)
394 {
395  int n, val;
396  socklen_t len;
397 
398  val = size;
399  len = sizeof (int);
400  if (getsockopt (fd, SOL_SOCKET, SO_SNDBUF, (char *) &val, &len) < 0)
401  {
402  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to getsockopt(%d, SO_SND_BUF, %d, %d). " "(errno:%d).", fd, val, len,
403  errno);
404  return -1;
405  }
406  if (val < size)
407  {
408  val = size;
409  len = sizeof (int);
410  setsockopt (fd, SOL_SOCKET, SO_SNDBUF, (char *) &val, len);
411  }
412 
413  val = size;
414  len = sizeof (int);
415  if (getsockopt (fd, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVBUF, (char *) &val, &len) < 0)
416  {
417  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to getsockopt(%d, SO_RCV_BUF, %d, %d). " "(errno:%d).", fd, val, len,
418  errno);
419 
420  return -1;
421  }
422  if (val < size)
423  {
424  val = size;
425  len = sizeof (int);
426  setsockopt (fd, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVBUF, (char *) &val, len);
427  }
428 
429  return 1;
430 }
431 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */

506 int
507 proxy_make_net_buf (T_NET_BUF * net_buf, int size, T_BROKER_VERSION client_version)
508 {
509  net_buf_init (net_buf, client_version);
510 
511  net_buf->data = (char *) MALLOC (size);
512  if (net_buf->data == NULL)
513  {
514  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR,
515  "Not enough virtual memory. " "Failed to alloc net buffer. " "(errno:%d, size:%d).", errno, size);
516  return -1;
517  }
518  net_buf->alloc_size = size;
519 
520  return 0;
521 }

523 static void
524 proxy_init_net_buf (T_NET_BUF * net_buf)
525 {
526  MSG_HEADER msg_header;
527 
528  assert (net_buf);
529  assert (net_buf->data);
530 
531  init_msg_header (&msg_header);
532 
533  *(msg_header.msg_body_size_ptr) = htonl (net_buf->data_size);
534 
535  /* length */
536  memcpy (net_buf->data, msg_header.buf, NET_BUF_HEADER_MSG_SIZE);
537 
538  /* cas info */
539  /* 0:cas status */
540  msg_header.info_ptr[CAS_INFO_STATUS] = CAS_INFO_STATUS_INACTIVE;
541 
542  /* 3:cci default autocommit */
543  msg_header.info_ptr[CAS_INFO_ADDITIONAL_FLAG] &= ~CAS_INFO_FLAG_MASK_AUTOCOMMIT;
544  msg_header.info_ptr[CAS_INFO_ADDITIONAL_FLAG] |= (shm_as_p->cci_default_autocommit & CAS_INFO_FLAG_MASK_AUTOCOMMIT);
545 
546  msg_header.info_ptr[CAS_INFO_ADDITIONAL_FLAG] &= ~CAS_INFO_FLAG_MASK_NEW_SESSION_ID;
547 
548  memcpy (net_buf->data + NET_BUF_HEADER_MSG_SIZE, msg_header.info_ptr, CAS_INFO_SIZE);
549 
550  return;
551 }

553 static int
554 proxy_io_make_ex_get_int (char *driver_info, char **buffer, int *argv)
555 {
556  int error;
557  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
558  T_BROKER_VERSION client_version;
559 
560  assert (buffer);
561  assert (*buffer == NULL);
562  assert (argv != NULL);
563 
564  client_version = CAS_MAKE_PROTO_VER (driver_info);
565 
566  error = proxy_make_net_buf (&net_buf, SHARD_NET_BUF_ALLOC_SIZE, client_version);
567  if (error)
568  {
569  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to make net buffer. (error:%d).", error);
570  goto error_return;
571  }
572 
573  proxy_init_net_buf (&net_buf);
574 
575  /* error code */
576  net_buf_cp_int (&net_buf, 0 /* success */ , NULL);
577  /* int arg1 */
578  net_buf_cp_int (&net_buf, *argv, NULL);
579 
580  *buffer = net_buf.data;
581  set_data_length (*buffer, net_buf.data_size);
582 
583  net_buf.data = NULL;
584 
585  return (net_buf.data_size + MSG_HEADER_SIZE);
586 
587 error_return:
588  *buffer = NULL;
589 
590  return -1;
591 }

593 /* error */
594 int
595 proxy_io_make_error_msg (char *driver_info, char **buffer, int error_ind, int error_code, const char *error_msg,
596  char is_in_tran)
597 {
598  int error;
599  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
600  T_BROKER_VERSION client_version;
601 
602  assert (buffer);
603  assert (*buffer == NULL);
604 
605  client_version = CAS_MAKE_PROTO_VER (driver_info);
606 
607  error = proxy_make_net_buf (&net_buf, SHARD_NET_BUF_ALLOC_SIZE, client_version);
608  if (error)
609  {
610  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to make net buffer. " "(error:%d).", error);
611  goto error_return;
612  }
613 
614  proxy_init_net_buf (&net_buf);
615 
616  if (is_in_tran)
617  {
618  proxy_set_con_status_in_tran (net_buf.data);
619  }
620 
621  if (error_ind != CAS_NO_ERROR)
622  {
623  if (client_version >= CAS_MAKE_VER (8, 3, 0))
624  {
625  /* error indicator */
626  net_buf_cp_int (&net_buf, error_ind, NULL);
627  }
628  }
629 
630  error_code = proxy_convert_error_code (error_ind, error_code, driver_info, client_version, PROXY_CONV_ERR_TO_OLD);
631 
632  /* error code */
633  net_buf_cp_int (&net_buf, error_code, NULL);
634 
635  if (error_msg && error_msg[0])
636  {
637  /* error messgae */
638  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, error_msg, strlen (error_msg) + 1);
639  }
640 
641  *buffer = net_buf.data;
642  set_data_length (*buffer, net_buf.data_size);
643 
644  net_buf.data = NULL;
645 
646  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("make error to send to the client. " "(error_ind:%d, error_code:%d, errro_msg:%s)", error_ind,
647  error_code, (error_msg && error_msg[0]) ? error_msg : "-");
648 
649  return (net_buf.data_size + MSG_HEADER_SIZE);
650 
651 error_return:
652  *buffer = NULL;
653 
654  return -1;
655 }

916 proxy_io_make_client_dbinfo_ok (char *driver_info, char **buffer)
917 {

921  int cas_info_size;

925

927

929 
930  client_version = CAS_MAKE_PROTO_VER (driver_info);
931  if (DOES_CLIENT_UNDERSTAND_THE_PROTOCOL (client_version, PROTOCOL_V5))
932  {
933  if (proxy_info_p->appl_server == APPL_SERVER_CAS_ORACLE)
934  {
935  dbms_type = CAS_PROXY_DBMS_ORACLE;
936  }
937  else if (proxy_info_p->appl_server == APPL_SERVER_CAS_MYSQL
938  || proxy_info_p->appl_server == APPL_SERVER_CAS_MYSQL51)
939  {
940  dbms_type = CAS_PROXY_DBMS_MYSQL;
941  }
942  else
943  {
944  dbms_type = CAS_PROXY_DBMS_CUBRID;
945  }
946  }
947  else
948  {
949  dbms_type = CAS_DBMS_CUBRID;
950  }
951 
952  cas_bi_make_broker_info (broker_info, dbms_type, shm_as_p->statement_pooling, shm_as_p->cci_pconnect);
953 
954  if (DOES_CLIENT_UNDERSTAND_THE_PROTOCOL (client_version, PROTOCOL_V4))
955  {
956  reply_size = CAS_CONNECTION_REPLY_SIZE;
957  }
958  else if (DOES_CLIENT_UNDERSTAND_THE_PROTOCOL (client_version, PROTOCOL_V3))
959  {
960  reply_size = CAS_CONNECTION_REPLY_SIZE_V3;
961  }
962  else
963  {
964  reply_size = CAS_CONNECTION_REPLY_SIZE_PRIOR_PROTOCOL_V3;
965  }
966 
967  *buffer = (char *) malloc (PROXY_CONNECTION_REPLY_SIZE (reply_size) * sizeof (char));
968  if (*buffer == NULL)
969  {
970  return -1;
971  }
972 
973  reply_nsize = htonl (reply_size);
974  cas_info_size = htonl (CAS_INFO_SIZE);
975  proxy_pid = htonl (getpid ());
976 
977  /* length */
978  p = *(buffer);
979  memcpy (p, &reply_nsize, PROTOCOL_SIZE);
980  p += PROTOCOL_SIZE;
981 
982  /* cas info */
983  memcpy (p, &cas_info_size, CAS_INFO_SIZE);
984  p += CAS_INFO_SIZE;
985 
986  /* proxy pid */
987  memcpy (p, &proxy_pid, CAS_PID_SIZE);
988  p += CAS_PID_SIZE;
989 
990  /* brokerinfo */
991  memcpy (p, broker_info, BROKER_INFO_SIZE);
992  p += BROKER_INFO_SIZE;
993 
994  /* proxy id */
995  if (DOES_CLIENT_UNDERSTAND_THE_PROTOCOL (client_version, PROTOCOL_V4))
996  {
997  int v = htonl (proxy_id + 1);
998 
999  memcpy (p, &v, CAS_PID_SIZE);
1000  p += CAS_PID_SIZE;
1001  }
1002 
1003  /* session id */
1004  if (DOES_CLIENT_UNDERSTAND_THE_PROTOCOL (client_version, PROTOCOL_V3))
1005  {
1006  memset ((char *) p, 0, DRIVER_SESSION_SIZE);
1007  p += DRIVER_SESSION_SIZE;
1008  }
1009  else
1010  {
1011  memset ((char *) p, 0, SESSION_ID_SIZE);
1012  p += SESSION_ID_SIZE;
1013  }
1014 
1015  return PROXY_CONNECTION_REPLY_SIZE (reply_size);
1016 }

1169 static int
1170 proxy_socket_io_initialize (void)
1171 {
1172  int i;
1173  int size;
1174  T_SOCKET_IO *sock_io_p;
1175 
1176  if (proxy_Socket_io.ent)
1177  {
1178  /* alredy initialized */
1179  return 0;
1180  }
1181 
1182 #if defined(LINUX)
1183  proxy_Socket_io.max_socket = max_Socket;
1184 #else /* LINUX */
1185  proxy_Socket_io.max_socket = MAX_FD;
1186 #endif /* !LINUX */
1187  proxy_Socket_io.cur_socket = 0;
1188 
1189  size = sizeof (T_SOCKET_IO) * proxy_Socket_io.max_socket;
1190  proxy_Socket_io.ent = (T_SOCKET_IO *) malloc (size);
1191  if (proxy_Socket_io.ent == NULL)
1192  {
1193  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR,
1194  "Not enough virtual memory. " "Failed to alloc socket entry. " "(errno:%d, size:%d).", errno, size);
1195  return -1;
1196  }
1197  memset (proxy_Socket_io.ent, 0, size);
1198 
1199  for (i = 0; i < proxy_Socket_io.max_socket; i++)
1200  {
1201  sock_io_p = &(proxy_Socket_io.ent[i]);
1202 
1203  proxy_socket_io_clear (sock_io_p);
1204  }
1205 
1206  return 0;
1207 }
1208 
1209 static void
1210 proxy_socket_io_destroy (void)
1211 {
1212  int i;
1213  T_SOCKET_IO *sock_io_p;
1214 
1215  if (proxy_Socket_io.ent == NULL)
1216  {
1217  return;
1218  }
1219 
1220  for (i = 0; i < proxy_Socket_io.max_socket; i++)
1221  {
1222  sock_io_p = &(proxy_Socket_io.ent[i]);
1223 
1224  if (sock_io_p->fd != INVALID_SOCKET)
1225  {
1226 #if defined(LINUX)
1227  if (sock_io_p->status != SOCK_IO_CLOSE_WAIT)
1228  {
1229  (void) proxy_del_epoll_event (sock_io_p->fd);
1230  }
1231 #else /* LINUX */
1232  FD_CLR (sock_io_p->fd, &allset);
1233  FD_CLR (sock_io_p->fd, &wnewset);
1234 #endif /* !LINUX */
1235  CLOSE_SOCKET (sock_io_p->fd);
1236  }
1237  proxy_socket_io_clear (sock_io_p);
1238  }
1239 
1240  proxy_Socket_io.max_socket = 0;
1241  proxy_Socket_io.cur_socket = 0;
1242  FREE_MEM (proxy_Socket_io.ent);
1243 
1244  return;
1245 }

1274  client_id = PROXY_INVALID_CAS;
1275  shard_id = sock_io_p->id.shard.shard_id;
1276  cas_id = sock_io_p->id.shard.cas_id;
1277  from_cas = (char *) "cas";
1278  }
1279  else
1280  {
1281  client_id = sock_io_p->id.client_id;
1282  shard_id = PROXY_INVALID_SHARD;
1283  cas_id = PROXY_INVALID_CAS;
1284  from_cas = (char *) "client";
1285  }
1286 
1287  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_SCHEDULE_DETAIL, "[%-5d] %-5d %-8d %-16s %-8s %-10d %-10d %-10d", i,
1288  sock_io_p->fd, sock_io_p->status, inet_ntoa (*((struct in_addr *) &sock_io_p->ip_addr)), from_cas,
1289  client_id, shard_id, cas_id);
1290 
1291  }
1292  }
1293 
1294  return;
1295 }
1296 #endif /* PROXY_VERBOSE_DEBUG */
1297 
1298 static T_SOCKET_IO *
1299 proxy_socket_io_add (SOCKET fd, bool from_cas)
1300 {
1301 #if defined(LINUX)
1302  int error;
1303 #endif
1304  T_SOCKET_IO *sock_io_p;
1305 
1306  assert (proxy_Socket_io.ent);
1307  if (proxy_Socket_io.ent == NULL)
1308  {
1309  return NULL;
1310  }
1311 
1312  if (fd >= proxy_Socket_io.max_socket)
1313  {
1314  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "socket fd exceeds max socket fd. (fd:%d, max socket fd:%d).", fd,
1315  proxy_Socket_io.max_socket);
1316  return NULL;
1317  }
1318 
1319  if (proxy_Socket_io.cur_socket >= proxy_Socket_io.max_socket)
1320  {
1321  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR,
1322  "Number of socket entry exceeds max_socket. " "(current_socket:%d, max_socket:%d).",
1323  proxy_Socket_io.cur_socket, proxy_Socket_io.max_socket);
1324  return NULL;
1325  }
1326 
1327  sock_io_p = &(proxy_Socket_io.ent[fd]);
1328 
1329  if (sock_io_p->fd > INVALID_SOCKET || sock_io_p->status != SOCK_IO_IDLE)
1330  {
1331  assert (false);
1332  proxy_Keep_running = false;
1333  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Receive duplicated socket fd. " "(received socket:%d, status:%d)",
1334  sock_io_p->fd, sock_io_p->status);
1335  return NULL;
1336  }
1337 
1338  shard_io_set_fl (fd, O_NONBLOCK);
1339 
1340 #if defined(LINUX)
1341  error = proxy_add_epoll_event (fd, EPOLLIN | EPOLLOUT);
1342  if (error < 0)
1343  {
1344  CLOSE_SOCKET (fd);
1345  return NULL;
1346  }
1347 #else /* LINUX */
1348  FD_SET (fd, &allset);
1349  maxfd = max (maxfd, fd);
1350 #endif /* !LINUX */
1351 
1352  sock_io_p->fd = fd;
1353  sock_io_p->status = SOCK_IO_REG_WAIT;
1354  sock_io_p->ip_addr = 0;
1355 
1356  sock_io_p->from_cas = from_cas;
1357 
1358  sock_io_p->id.shard.shard_id = PROXY_INVALID_SHARD;
1359  sock_io_p->id.shard.cas_id = PROXY_INVALID_CAS;
1360 
1361  assert (sock_io_p->read_event == NULL);
1362  assert (sock_io_p->write_event == NULL);
1363  sock_io_p->read_event = NULL;
1364  sock_io_p->write_event = NULL;
1365 
1366  proxy_Socket_io.cur_socket++;
1367 
1368  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_SHARD_DETAIL, "New socket io created. (fd:%d).", fd);
1369 #if defined(PROXY_VERBOSE_DEBUG)
1370  proxy_socket_io_print (false);
1371 #endif /* PROXY_VERBOSE_DEBUG */
1372 
1373  return sock_io_p;
1374 }

1376 int
1377 proxy_socket_io_delete (SOCKET fd)
1378 {
1379  T_SOCKET_IO *sock_io_p;
1380 
1381  ENTER_FUNC ();
1382 
1383  assert (proxy_Socket_io.ent);
1384  assert (proxy_Socket_io.cur_socket > 0);
1385 
1386  if (fd >= proxy_Socket_io.max_socket)
1387  {
1388  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "socket fd exceeds max socket fd. (fd:%d, max_socket_fd:%d).", fd,
1389  proxy_Socket_io.max_socket);
1390  EXIT_FUNC ();
1391  return -1;
1392  }
1393 
1394  sock_io_p = &(proxy_Socket_io.ent[fd]);
1395 
1396  if (sock_io_p->fd != INVALID_SOCKET)
1397  {
1398 #if defined(LINUX)
1399  if (sock_io_p->status != SOCK_IO_CLOSE_WAIT)
1400  {
1401  (void) proxy_del_epoll_event (sock_io_p->fd);
1402  }
1403 #else /* LINUX */
1404  FD_CLR (sock_io_p->fd, &allset);
1405  FD_CLR (sock_io_p->fd, &wnewset);
1406 #endif /* !LINUX */
1407 
1408  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("Close socket. (fd:%d).", sock_io_p->fd);
1409  CLOSE_SOCKET (sock_io_p->fd);
1410  }
1411  proxy_socket_io_clear (sock_io_p);
1412  proxy_Socket_io.cur_socket--;
1413 
1414  EXIT_FUNC ();
1415  return 0;
1416 }

1453 int
1454 proxy_socket_set_write_event (T_SOCKET_IO * sock_io_p, T_PROXY_EVENT * event_p)
1455 {
1456 #if defined(LINUX)
1457  int error;
1458 #endif
1459 
1460  assert (sock_io_p);
1461  assert (event_p);
1462 
1463  if (sock_io_p->write_event)
1464  {
1465  /* the procotol between driver and proxy must be broken */
1466  goto error_return;
1467  }
1468 
1469 #if defined(LINUX)
1470  error = proxy_mod_epoll_event (sock_io_p->fd, EPOLLIN | EPOLLOUT);
1471  if (error < 0)
1472  {
1473  goto error_return;
1474  }
1475 #else /* LINUX */
1476  FD_SET (sock_io_p->fd, &wnewset);
1477 #endif /* !LINUX */
1478 
1479  event_p->buffer.offset = 0; // set offset to start of the write buffer
1480  sock_io_p->write_event = event_p;
1481 
1482  return 0;
1483 
1484 error_return:
1485 
1486  if (sock_io_p->write_event)
1487  {
1488  proxy_event_free (sock_io_p->write_event);
1489  sock_io_p->write_event = NULL;
1490  }
1491  return -1;
1492 }

1494 static int
1495 proxy_socket_io_new_client (SOCKET lsnr_fd)
1496 {
1497  int client_ip;
1498  SOCKET client_fd;
1499  T_CLIENT_IO *cli_io_p;
1500  T_SOCKET_IO *sock_io_p;
1501  T_CLIENT_INFO *client_info_p;
1502  int proxy_status = 0;
1503  char driver_info[SRV_CON_CLIENT_INFO_SIZE];
1504 #if !defined (WINDOWS)
1505  T_PROXY_EVENT *event_p;
1506  int length;
1507  int error;
1508 #endif
1509 
1510  proxy_info_p->num_connect_requests++;
1511 
1512 #if defined(WINDOWS)
1513  client_fd = lsnr_fd;
1514  client_ip = accept_ip_addr;
1515  memset (driver_info, 0, SRV_CON_CLIENT_INFO_SIZE);
1516  driver_info[SRV_CON_MSG_IDX_PROTO_VERSION] = CAS_PROTO_UNPACK_NET_VER (PROTOCOL_V4);
1517  driver_info[SRV_CON_MSG_IDX_FUNCTION_FLAG] = BROKER_RENEWED_ERROR_CODE | BROKER_SUPPORT_HOLDABLE_RESULT;
1518 #else /* WINDOWS */
1519  client_fd = recv_fd (lsnr_fd, &client_ip, driver_info);
1520  if (client_fd < 0)
1521  {
1522  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to receive socket fd. " "(lsnf_fd:%d, client_fd:%d).", lsnr_fd,
1523  client_fd);
1524 
1525  /* shard_broker must be abnormal status */
1526  proxy_Keep_running = false;
1527  return -1;
1528  }
1529 
1530  proxy_status = 0;
1531  length = WRITESOCKET (lsnr_fd, &proxy_status, sizeof (proxy_status));
1532  if (length != sizeof (proxy_status))
1533  {
1534  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to send proxy status to broker. " "(lsnr_fd:%d).", lsnr_fd);
1535  CLOSE_SOCKET (client_fd);
1536  return -1;
1537  }
1538 #endif /* !WINDOWS */
1539 
1540  ENTER_FUNC ();
1541 
1542  sock_io_p = proxy_socket_io_add (client_fd, PROXY_IO_FROM_CLIENT);
1543  if (sock_io_p == NULL)
1544  {
1545  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to add socket entry. (client fd:%d).", client_fd);
1546  CLOSE_SOCKET (client_fd);
1547  return -1;
1548  }
1549 
1550  cli_io_p = proxy_client_io_new (client_fd, driver_info);
1551  if (cli_io_p == NULL)
1552  {
1553  proxy_socket_io_delete (client_fd);
1554  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to create client entry. (client fd:%d).", client_fd);
1555  return -1;
1556  }
1557 
1558  sock_io_p->ip_addr = client_ip;
1559  sock_io_p->id.client_id = cli_io_p->client_id;
1560 
1561  /* set shared memory T_CLIENT_INFO */
1562  client_info_p = shard_shm_get_client_info (proxy_info_p, cli_io_p->client_id);
1563  client_info_p->client_id = cli_io_p->client_id;
1564  client_info_p->client_ip = client_ip;
1565  client_info_p->connect_time = time (NULL);
1566  memcpy (client_info_p->driver_info, cli_io_p->driver_info, SRV_CON_CLIENT_INFO_SIZE);
1567 
1568 #if !defined(WINDOWS)
1569  /* send client_conn_ok to the client */
1570  event_p =
1571  proxy_event_new_with_rsp (cli_io_p->driver_info, PROXY_EVENT_IO_WRITE, PROXY_EVENT_FROM_CLIENT,
1572  proxy_io_make_client_conn_ok);
1573  if (event_p == NULL)
1574  {
1575  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
1576  EXIT_FUNC ();
1577  return -1;
1578  }
1579 
1580  /* set write event to the socket io */
1581  error = proxy_socket_set_write_event (sock_io_p, event_p);
1582  if (error)
1583  {
1584  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to set write buffer. " "(fd:%d). event(%s).", client_fd,
1585  proxy_str_event (event_p));
1586 
1587  proxy_event_free (event_p);
1588  event_p = NULL;
1589 
1590  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
1591 
1592  EXIT_FUNC ();
1593  return -1;
1594  }
1595 #endif /* !WINDOWS */
1596 
1597  EXIT_FUNC ();
1598 
1599  return 0;
1600 }
1601 
1602 static int
1603 proxy_process_client_register (T_SOCKET_IO * sock_io_p)
1604 {
1605  int error = 0;
1606  char *db_name = NULL, *db_user = NULL, *db_passwd = NULL;
1607  char *url = NULL, *db_sessionid = NULL;
1608  struct timeval client_start_time;
1609  T_PROXY_CONTEXT *ctx_p;
1610  T_IO_BUFFER *read_buffer;
1611  T_PROXY_EVENT *event_p;
1612  T_CLIENT_INFO *client_info_p;
1613  unsigned char *ip_addr;
1614  char len;
1615  char *driver_info;
1616  T_BROKER_VERSION client_version;
1617  char driver_version[SRV_CON_VER_STR_MAX_SIZE];
1618  char err_msg[256];
1619 
1620  ENTER_FUNC ();
1621 
1622  assert (sock_io_p);
1623  assert (sock_io_p->read_event);
1624 
1625  driver_info = proxy_get_driver_info_by_fd (sock_io_p);
1626 
1627  gettimeofday (&client_start_time, NULL);
1628 
1629  read_buffer = &(sock_io_p->read_event->buffer);
1630  assert (read_buffer); // __FOR_DEBUG
1631 
1632  db_name = read_buffer->data;
1633  db_name[SRV_CON_DBNAME_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
1634 
1635  ctx_p = proxy_context_find_by_socket_client_io (sock_io_p);
1636  if (ctx_p == NULL)
1637  {
1638  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to find context for this socket. (fd:%d)", sock_io_p->fd);
1639  error = -1;
1640  goto clear_event_and_return;
1641  }
1642 
1643  if (ctx_p->error_ind != CAS_NO_ERROR)
1644  {
1645  /* Skip authorization and process error */
1646  goto connection_established;
1647  }
1648 
1649  if (strcmp (db_name, HEALTH_CHECK_DUMMY_DB) == 0)
1650  {
1651  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("Incoming health check request from client.");
1652  /* send proxy_alive response to the client */
1653  event_p =
1654  proxy_event_new_with_rsp (driver_info, PROXY_EVENT_IO_WRITE, PROXY_EVENT_FROM_CLIENT,
1655  proxy_io_make_client_proxy_alive);
1656  if (event_p == NULL)
1657  {
1658  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
1659  EXIT_FUNC ();
1660  return -1;
1661  }
1662 
1663  /* set write event to the socket io */
1664  error = proxy_socket_set_write_event (sock_io_p, event_p);
1665  if (error)
1666  {
1667  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to set write buffer. " "(fd:%d). event(%s).", sock_io_p->fd,
1668  proxy_str_event (event_p));
1669 
1670  proxy_event_free (event_p);
1671  event_p = NULL;
1672 
1673  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
1674  EXIT_FUNC ();
1675  return -1;
1676  }
1677  goto clear_event_and_return;
1678  }
1679 
1680  db_user = db_name + SRV_CON_DBNAME_SIZE;
1681  db_user[SRV_CON_DBUSER_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
1682  if (db_user[0] == '\0')
1683  {
1684  strcpy (db_user, "PUBLIC");
1685  }
1686 
1687  db_passwd = db_user + SRV_CON_DBUSER_SIZE;
1688  db_passwd[SRV_CON_DBPASSWD_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
1689 
1690  client_version = CAS_MAKE_PROTO_VER (driver_info);
1691  if (client_version >= CAS_MAKE_VER (8, 2, 0))
1692  {
1693  url = db_passwd + SRV_CON_DBPASSWD_SIZE;
1694  url[SRV_CON_URL_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
1695  driver_version[0] = '\0';
1696  if (DOES_CLIENT_UNDERSTAND_THE_PROTOCOL (client_version, PROTOCOL_V5))
1697  {
1698  len = *(url + strlen (url) + 1);
1699  if (len > 0 && len < SRV_CON_VER_STR_MAX_SIZE)
1700  {
1701  memcpy (driver_version, url + strlen (url) + 2, (int) len);
1702  driver_version[(int) len] = '\0';
1703  }
1704  else
1705  {
1706  snprintf (driver_version, SRV_CON_VER_STR_MAX_SIZE, "PROTOCOL V%d",
1707  (int) (CAS_PROTO_VER_MASK & client_version));
1708  }
1709  }
1710  else if (DOES_CLIENT_UNDERSTAND_THE_PROTOCOL (client_version, PROTOCOL_V1))
1711  {
1712  char *ver;
1713 
1714  CAS_PROTO_TO_VER_STR (&ver, (int) (CAS_PROTO_VER_MASK & client_version));
1715 
1716  strncpy (driver_version, ver, SRV_CON_VER_STR_MAX_SIZE);
1717  }
1718  else
1719  {
1720  snprintf (driver_version, SRV_CON_VER_STR_MAX_SIZE, "%d.%d.%d", CAS_VER_TO_MAJOR (client_version),
1721  CAS_VER_TO_MINOR (client_version), CAS_VER_TO_PATCH (client_version));
1722  }
1723  client_info_p = shard_shm_get_client_info (proxy_info_p, sock_io_p->id.client_id);
1724  if (client_info_p)
1725  {
1726  memcpy (client_info_p->driver_version, driver_version, sizeof (driver_version));
1727  }
1728  }
1729 
1730  /* SHARD DO NOT SUPPORT SESSION */
1731  if (client_version >= CAS_MAKE_VER (8, 4, 0))
1732  {
1733  db_sessionid = url + SRV_CON_URL_SIZE;
1734  db_sessionid[SRV_CON_DBSESS_ID_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
1735  }
1736 
1737  ip_addr = (unsigned char *) (&sock_io_p->ip_addr);
1738 
1739  /* check acl */
1740  if (shm_as_p->access_control)
1741  {
1742  if (access_control_check_right (shm_as_p, db_name, db_user, ip_addr) < 0)
1743  {
1744  proxy_info_p->num_connect_rejected++;
1745 
1746  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg), "Authorization error.(Address is rejected)");
1747  proxy_context_set_error_with_msg (ctx_p, DBMS_ERROR_INDICATOR, CAS_ER_NOT_AUTHORIZED_CLIENT, err_msg);
1748 
1749  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Authentication failure. " "(db_name:[%s], db_user:[%s], db_passwd:[%s]).",
1750  db_name, db_user, db_passwd);
1751 
1752  if (shm_as_p->access_log == ON)
1753  {
1754  proxy_access_log (&client_start_time, sock_io_p->ip_addr, (db_name) ? (const char *) db_name : "-",
1755  (db_user) ? (const char *) db_user : "-", true);
1756  }
1757 
1758  goto connection_established;
1759  }
1760  }
1761 
1762  error = proxy_check_authorization (ctx_p, db_name, db_user, db_passwd);
1763  if (error < 0)
1764  {
1765  goto connection_established;
1766  }
1767 
1768  strncpy (ctx_p->database_user, db_user, SRV_CON_DBUSER_SIZE - 1);
1769  strncpy (ctx_p->database_passwd, db_passwd, SRV_CON_DBPASSWD_SIZE - 1);
1770 
1771  if (proxy_info_p->fixed_shard_user == false)
1772  {
1773  event_p =
1774  proxy_event_new_with_rsp (driver_info, PROXY_EVENT_CLIENT_REQUEST, PROXY_EVENT_FROM_CLIENT,
1775  proxy_io_make_check_cas);
1776  if (event_p == NULL)
1777  {
1778  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
1779 
1780  EXIT_FUNC ();
1781  return -1;
1782  }
1783 
1784  proxy_event_set_context (event_p, ctx_p->cid, ctx_p->uid);
1785 
1786  error = shard_queue_enqueue (&proxy_Handler.cli_rcv_q, (void *) event_p);
1787  if (error)
1788  {
1789  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to queue client event. " "context(%s). event(%s).",
1790  proxy_str_context (ctx_p), proxy_str_event (event_p));
1791 
1792  proxy_event_free (event_p);
1793  event_p = NULL;
1794 
1795  proxy_context_free (ctx_p);
1796 
1797  EXIT_FUNC ();
1798  return -1;
1799  }
1800 
1801  goto clear_event_and_return;
1802  }
1803 
1804 connection_established:
1805  if (ctx_p->error_ind != CAS_NO_ERROR)
1806  {
1807  /*
1808  * Process error message if exists.
1809  * context will be freed after sending error message.
1810  */
1811  proxy_context_send_error (ctx_p);
1812  proxy_context_clear_error (ctx_p);
1813 
1814  ctx_p->free_on_client_io_write = true;
1815  }
1816  else
1817  {
1818  /* send dbinfo_ok to the client */
1819  event_p =
1820  proxy_event_new_with_rsp (driver_info, PROXY_EVENT_IO_WRITE, PROXY_EVENT_FROM_CLIENT,
1821  proxy_io_make_client_dbinfo_ok);
1822  if (event_p == NULL)
1823  {
1824  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
1825  EXIT_FUNC ();
1826  return -1;
1827  }
1828 
1829  /* set write event to the socket io */
1830  error = proxy_socket_set_write_event (sock_io_p, event_p);
1831  if (error)
1832  {
1833  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to set write buffer. " "(fd:%d). event(%s).", sock_io_p->fd,
1834  proxy_str_event (event_p));
1835 
1836  proxy_event_free (event_p);
1837  event_p = NULL;
1838 
1839  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
1840  EXIT_FUNC ();
1841  return -1;
1842  }
1843 
1844  ctx_p->is_connected = true;
1845 
1846  sock_io_p->status = SOCK_IO_ESTABLISHED;
1847 
1848  if (shm_as_p->access_log == ON)
1849  {
1850  proxy_access_log (&client_start_time, sock_io_p->ip_addr, (db_name) ? (const char *) db_name : "-",
1851  (db_user) ? (const char *) db_user : "-", true);
1852  }
1853  }
1854 
1855 clear_event_and_return:

2055 static int
2056 proxy_process_cas_register (T_SOCKET_IO * sock_io_p)
2057 {
2058  int length;
2059  char *p;
2060  int shard_id = PROXY_INVALID_SHARD, cas_id = PROXY_INVALID_CAS;
2061  char func_code;
2062  T_SHARD_IO *shard_io_p = NULL;
2063  T_CAS_IO *cas_io_p = NULL;
2064  T_IO_BUFFER *read_buffer;
2065 
2066  ENTER_FUNC ();
2067 
2068  assert (sock_io_p);
2069  assert (sock_io_p->read_event);
2070 
2071  read_buffer = &(sock_io_p->read_event->buffer);
2072 
2073  length = get_msg_length (read_buffer->data);
2074  assert (read_buffer->offset == length);
2075 
2076  /* func code */
2077  p = (char *) (read_buffer->data + MSG_HEADER_SIZE);
2078  memcpy (&func_code, p, sizeof (char));
2079  p += sizeof (char);
2080 
2081  /* shard id */
2082  memcpy (&shard_id, p, sizeof (int));
2083  shard_id = ntohl (shard_id);
2084  p += sizeof (int);
2085 
2086  memcpy (&cas_id, p, sizeof (int));
2087  cas_id = ntohl (cas_id);
2088 
2089  cas_io_p = proxy_cas_io_new (shard_id, cas_id, sock_io_p->fd);
2090  if (cas_io_p == NULL)
2091  {
2092  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to create CAS entry. " "(shard_id:%d, cas_id:%d, fd:%d).", shard_id,
2093  cas_id, sock_io_p->fd);
2094  goto error_return;
2095  }
2096  assert (sock_io_p->from_cas == PROXY_EVENT_FROM_CAS);
2097 
2098  /* fill socket io entry */
2099  sock_io_p->status = SOCK_IO_ESTABLISHED;
2100  sock_io_p->id.shard.shard_id = shard_id;
2101  sock_io_p->id.shard.cas_id = cas_id;
2102 
2103  /* SHARD TODO : !!! check protocol */
2104 
2105 
2106  shard_io_p = proxy_shard_io_find (shard_id);
2107  assert (shard_io_p);
2108 
2109  /* set cas io status */
2110  cas_io_p->status = CAS_IO_CONNECTED;
2111 
2112  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("New CAS registered. (shard_id:%d). CAS(%s).", shard_io_p->shard_id, proxy_str_cas_io (cas_io_p));
2113 
2114  proxy_client_check_waiter_and_wakeup (shard_io_p, cas_io_p);
2115 
2116  /* in this case, we should free event now */
2117  proxy_event_free (sock_io_p->read_event);
2118  sock_io_p->read_event = NULL;
2119 
2120  EXIT_FUNC ();
2121  return 0;
2122 
2123 error_return:
2124 
2125  /* in this case, we should free event now */
2126  proxy_event_free (sock_io_p->read_event);
2127  sock_io_p->read_event = NULL;
2128 
2129  if (cas_io_p && shard_id >= 0 && cas_id >= 0)
2130  {
2131  proxy_cas_io_free (shard_id, cas_id);
2132  }
2133  else
2134  {
2135  /* cas have to retry register to proxy. */
2136  proxy_socket_io_delete (sock_io_p->fd);
2137  }
2138 
2139  EXIT_FUNC ();
2140  return -1;
2141 }

2406 static int
2407 proxy_socket_io_write_internal (T_SOCKET_IO * sock_io_p)
2408 {
2409  int write_len;
2410  int remain;
2411  char *p;
2412  T_IO_BUFFER *send_buffer;
2413 
2414  // __FOR_DEBUG
2415  assert (sock_io_p);
2416  assert (sock_io_p->write_event);
2417 
2418  send_buffer = &(sock_io_p->write_event->buffer);
2419 
2420  if (send_buffer->length == send_buffer->offset)
2421  {
2422  write_len = 0;
2423  goto write_end;
2424  }
2425  else if (send_buffer->length < send_buffer->offset)
2426  {
2427  assert (false);
2428 
2429  write_len = -1;
2430  goto write_end;
2431  }
2432 
2433  remain = send_buffer->length - send_buffer->offset;
2434 
2435  p = (char *) (send_buffer->data + send_buffer->offset);
2436 
2437  write_len = WRITESOCKET (sock_io_p->fd, p, remain);
2438  if (write_len < 0)
2439  {
2440 #if defined(WINDOWS)
2441  int error;
2442 
2443  error = WSAGetLastError ();
2444  if (error == WSAEWOULDBLOCK)
2445 #else
2446  if ((errno == EWOULDBLOCK) || (errno == EAGAIN) || (errno == EINTR))
2447 #endif
2448  {
2449 #if defined(LINUX)
2450  /* Nothing to do. epoll events has not been changed. */
2451 #else /* LINUX */
2452  FD_SET (sock_io_p->fd, &wnewset);
2453 #endif /* !LINUX */
2454  return 0;
2455  }
2456 
2457  goto write_end;
2458  }
2459 
2460  send_buffer->offset += write_len;
2461 
2462  if (send_buffer->offset < send_buffer->length)
2463  {
2464 #if defined(LINUX)
2465  /* Nothing to do. epoll events has not been changed. */
2466 #else /* LINUX */
2467  FD_SET (sock_io_p->fd, &wnewset);
2468 #endif /* !LINUX */
2469  return write_len;
2470  }
2471 
2472 write_end:
2473 
2474  proxy_event_free (sock_io_p->write_event);
2475  sock_io_p->write_event = NULL;
2476 
2477 #if defined(LINUX)
2478  (void) proxy_mod_epoll_event (sock_io_p->fd, EPOLLIN);
2479 #else /* LINUX */
2480  FD_CLR (sock_io_p->fd, &wnewset);
2481 #endif /* !LINUX */
2482 
2483  return write_len;
2484 }

2487 proxy_socket_io_write_to_cas (T_SOCKET_IO * sock_io_p)

2489  int len;
2490 
2491  assert (sock_io_p);
2492 
2493  len = proxy_socket_io_write_internal (sock_io_p);
2494  if (len < 0)
2495  {
2496  proxy_socket_io_write_error (sock_io_p);

2504 {
2505  int len;
2506  T_PROXY_CONTEXT *ctx_p;
2507  T_CLIENT_INFO *client_info_p;

2509  assert (sock_io_p);
2510 
2511  len = proxy_socket_io_write_internal (sock_io_p);

2535 static int
2536 proxy_socket_io_read_internal (T_SOCKET_IO * sock_io_p)
2537 {
2538  int error;
2539  int read_len, remain, total_len;
2540  char *buffer;
2541  T_IO_BUFFER *read_buffer;
2542 
2543  assert (sock_io_p);
2544  assert (sock_io_p->read_event);
2545 
2546 read_again:
2547 
2548  read_buffer = &(sock_io_p->read_event->buffer);
2549  buffer = (char *) (read_buffer->data + read_buffer->offset);
2550  remain = read_buffer->length - read_buffer->offset;
2551 
2552  read_len = READSOCKET (sock_io_p->fd, buffer, remain);
2553  if (read_len < 0)
2554  {
2555 #if defined(WINDOWS)
2556  error = WSAGetLastError ();
2557  if ((error == WSAECONNRESET) || (error == WSAECONNABORTED))
2558  {
2559  return -1; /* failed */
2560  }
2561  else if (error == WSAEWOULDBLOCK)
2562 #else
2563  if ((errno == EWOULDBLOCK) || (errno == EAGAIN) || (errno == EINTR))
2564 #endif
2565  {
2566  return 0; /* retry */
2567  }
2568  return -1; /* disconnected */
2569  }
2570  else if (read_len == 0)
2571  {
2572  return -1; /* disconnected */
2573  }
2574 
2575  read_buffer->offset += read_len;
2576 
2577  /* common message header */
2578  if (read_buffer->length == MSG_HEADER_SIZE && read_buffer->length == read_buffer->offset)
2579  {
2580  /* expand buffer to receive payload */
2581  total_len = get_msg_length (read_buffer->data);
2582  if (total_len == read_buffer->offset)
2583  {
2584  /* no more data */
2585  return read_buffer->offset;
2586  }
2587 
2588  error = proxy_event_realloc_buffer (sock_io_p->read_event, total_len);
2589  if (error)
2590  {
2591  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("Failed to realloc event buffer. (error:%d).", error);
2592  proxy_socket_io_read_error (sock_io_p);
2593  return -1;
2594  }
2595 
2596  goto read_again;
2597  }
2598 
2599  return read_len;
2600 }

3685  curr_shard_id = (unsigned int) shard_id;
3686  }
3687  else
3688  {
3689  curr_shard_id = (unsigned int) (last_shard_id + 1) % proxy_Shard_io.max_shard;
3690 
3691  last_shard_id = curr_shard_id;
3692  }
3693 
3694  shard_io_p = &(proxy_Shard_io.ent[curr_shard_id]);
3695  if (shard_io_p->cur_num_cas <= 0)
3696  {
3697  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR,
3698  "Failed to allocate shard/cas. " "No available cas in this shard. "
3699  "Wait until shard has available cas. " "(cur_num_cas:%d, max_num_cas:%d)", shard_io_p->cur_num_cas,
3700  shard_io_p->max_num_cas);
3701  }
3702 
3703  error = proxy_client_add_waiter_by_shard (shard_io_p, ctx_cid, ctx_uid, timeout);
3704  if (error)
3705  {
3706  return NULL;
3707  }
3708 
3709  return (T_CAS_IO *) (SHARD_TEMPORARY_UNAVAILABLE);
3710 }

3712 void
3713 proxy_cas_release_by_ctx (int shard_id, int cas_id, int ctx_cid, unsigned int ctx_uid)
3714 {
3715  T_SHARD_IO *shard_io_p;
3716  T_CAS_IO *cas_io_p;
3717 
3718  ENTER_FUNC ();
3719 
3720  if (0 > shard_id || shard_id >= proxy_Shard_io.max_shard)
3721  {
3722  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("Invalid shard id. (shard_id:%d, max_shard:%d).", shard_id, proxy_Shard_io.max_shard);
3723  EXIT_FUNC ();
3724  return;
3725  }
3726  shard_io_p = &(proxy_Shard_io.ent[shard_id]);
3727 
3728  if (0 > cas_id || cas_id >= shard_io_p->max_num_cas)
3729  {
3730  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Invalid CAS id. (cas_id:%d, max_num_cas:%d).", cas_id, shard_io_p->max_num_cas);
3731  EXIT_FUNC ();
3732  return;
3733  }
3734  cas_io_p = &(shard_io_p->ent[cas_id]);
3735 
3736  if (cas_io_p->is_in_tran == false || cas_io_p->ctx_cid != ctx_cid || cas_io_p->ctx_uid != ctx_uid)
3737  {
3738  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Unable to find CAS entry. " "(context id:%d, context uid:%d). CAS(%S).",
3739  ctx_cid, ctx_uid, proxy_str_cas_io (cas_io_p));
3740 
3741  assert (false);
3742 
3743  EXIT_FUNC ();
3744  return;
3745  }
3746 
3747  cas_io_p->is_in_tran = false;
3748  cas_io_p->ctx_cid = PROXY_INVALID_CONTEXT;
3749  cas_io_p->ctx_uid = 0;
3750 
3751  /* decrease number of cas in transaction */
3752  shard_io_p->num_cas_in_tran--;
3753 
3754  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("Shard status. (num_cas_in_tran=%d, shard_id=%d).", shard_io_p->num_cas_in_tran,
3755  shard_io_p->shard_id);
3756 
3757  assert (shard_io_p->num_cas_in_tran >= 0);
3758  if (shard_io_p->num_cas_in_tran < 0)
3759  {
3760  shard_io_p->num_cas_in_tran = 0;
3761  }
3762 
3763  /* check and wakeup shard/cas waiter */
3764  proxy_client_check_waiter_and_wakeup (shard_io_p, cas_io_p);
3765 
3766  EXIT_FUNC ();
3767  return;
3768 }

3809 static void
3810 proxy_client_check_waiter_and_wakeup (T_SHARD_IO * shard_io_p, T_CAS_IO * cas_io_p)
3811 {
3812  int error;
3813  T_WAIT_CONTEXT *waiter_p = NULL;
3814  T_SHARD_INFO *shard_info_p = NULL;
3815 
3816  ENTER_FUNC ();
3817 
3818  assert (shard_io_p);
3819  assert (cas_io_p);
3820 
3821  waiter_p = (T_WAIT_CONTEXT *) shard_queue_dequeue (&shard_io_p->waitq);
3822  while (waiter_p)
3823  {
3824  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("Wakeup waiter by shard. (shard_id:%d, cas_id:%d).", cas_io_p->shard_id, cas_io_p->cas_id);
3825 
3826  shard_info_p = shard_shm_find_shard_info (proxy_info_p, shard_io_p->shard_id);
3827  if ((shard_info_p != NULL) && (shard_info_p->waiter_count > 0))
3828  {
3829  shard_info_p->waiter_count--;
3830  PROXY_DEBUG_LOG ("Wakeup context by shard. (waiter_count:%d).", shard_info_p->waiter_count);
3831  }
3832 
3833  error = proxy_wakeup_context_by_shard (waiter_p, cas_io_p->shard_id, cas_io_p->cas_id);
3834  if (error)
3835  {
3836  PROXY_LOG (PROXY_LOG_MODE_ERROR, "Failed to wakeup context by shard. " "(error:%d, shard_id:%d, cas_id:%d).",
3837  error, cas_io_p->shard_id, cas_io_p->cas_id);
3838  FREE_MEM (waiter_p);
3839  continue;
3840  }
3841 
3842  FREE_MEM (waiter_p);
3843  break;
3844  }
3845 
3846  EXIT_FUNC ();
3847  return;
3848 }

4755 static T_CAS_IO *
4756 proxy_cas_alloc_anything (int client_id, int shard_id, int cas_id, int ctx_cid, unsigned int ctx_uid,
